rdata.shownotes: Thanks again to everyone who helped provide the semi-realtime setlists, I'll credit you admirably once everything's settled down.

comments.comment: Amazing show! My second radiohead concert, first was in Osaka 092901. They are never long enough! They could play all their songs and you wouldn't be satisfied! Forget about creep! Very fortunate to hear Street Spirit (fade out) & Bullet Proof...I wish I was. Great variety in setlist, great crowd, a can't miss show!
Creep? Yeah, that aint happening. I will see them in VA, if they play something similar to the two setlists I have seen, I will be happy.
any news on the opening act- liars? how long they played? any good? etc. thanks

This was my first Radiohead show EVER and I couldn't have been more lucky to see such a fantastic show.
It would have been nice if they didn't play as much of their newer stuff but, at least, they played the better tracks.
All in all, fantastic show!
all these songs are great, but they haven't been to tampa in 10 years or more so here's hoping for creep and fake plastic trees, karma police tonight !!

Great show. A bit a downtempo for my liking, but still great. The first encore was phenomenal and the new lighting setup is really great.
I can only complain about the lack of Paranoid Android and Jigsaw Falling Into Place.

I was there. One of the most amazing shows I have ever been to. The light show was absolutely stunning. I was disappointed they didn't play Karma Police, and not at all surprised that they didn't play Creep.
WOW Bullet Proof!! That's a tune not heard in a while
